OL,3,CHome Secretary commits to Hillsborough
OL,4,CLaw but unable to give timeframe
OL,6,FThe Home Secretary says a Hillsborough
OL,7,FLaw will be introduced, but would not
OL,8,Fcommit to a timeframe earlier laid out
OL,9,Fby the Prime Minister.
OL,11,FSpeaking exclusively to ITV News, on
OL,12,Fthe day Martyn's Law received Royal
OL,13,FAssent, the Home Secretary said:
OL,14,F"we've moved as speedily as we can"
OL,15,Fwhen asked about both bills.
OL,17,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer had
OL,18,Fpledged to introduce the so-called
OL,19,F"Hillsborough Law" before this year's
OL,20,Fanniversary of the tragedy, which took
OL,21,Fplace on April 15 1989.
